The paper deals with signal reconstruction from incomplete linear measurements, which is a common problem in signal processing and information theory. The use of prior support information is also a common technique in signal processing and compressive sensing. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of weighted $l_{1}$ minimization, which is a machine learning technique, and provides upper bounds on the reconstruction error, which is a statistical analysis. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), and cs.SI (Statistics) are also likely sub-categories.
